<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-54] Remove use of parent classloader in surefirebooter but keep TestNG support working</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-54</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The removal of the parent system classloader while running tests in surefire booter totally broke testNG support.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am going to revert the commit:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/surefire/trunk/surefire-booter/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/surefire/booter/SurefireBooter.java?r1=427040&amp;amp;r2=438999&amp;amp;diff_format=h&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/maven/surefire/trunk/surefire-booter/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/surefire/booter/SurefireBooter.java?r1=427040&amp;amp;r2=438999&amp;amp;diff_format=h&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
... in order to keep testng working for now, but we should find a way to solve both problems soon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The removal of the parent classloader is needed, according to Kenney for the following reason:&lt;br/&gt;
If this is not done, the System classloader is added, in this case an AppClassloader containing everything in the root classpath. For instance, in maven, everything in core/ is available.This can cause clashes with the plexus-utils used in maven itself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
